Oof. My wife and I have eaten at many Indian places (it is her favorite cuisine) and unfortunately this one is right at the bottom.  First off, two of our entrees were overly sweet. The vegetable korma was SO sweet that the sauce tasted like a vanilla cupcake. The chicken mahkani was on the verge of tasting like ketchup.  When my wife told the waiter that the korma that she ordered was too sweet and she didn't want to eat it, our waiter said "Kormas are sweet" and walked away.  Again, we've had a lot of kormas and none of them have ever been sweet. Sure, cashews have a sweetness to them but they don't taste like candy.  Very disappointing.

Pearl is an Indian restaurant that serves the usual dishes you would expect from any Indian restaurant but also Biryani dishes that are more specific to Muslim Indian places. As with many Indian restaurants, its menu is very vegetarian-friendly. I had a very good Kandhari naan there but the paneer tikka masala was only ok. The sauce had a strong tomato flavor but lacked other flavors. All in all a very decent meal and prices were ok. The host seemed a bit stressed especially when new customers arrived but the rest of the staff was very kind and friendly.

The quality of the food was pretty good. But the customer service there felt a little hostile. Namely with the tipping. They're pretty insistent that you give a good tip, which made me feel less inclined to give them that because of how they pressed me for it.

Since moving to Brooklyn a year ago, I have been looking for a good Indian restaurant similar to those you would find in Jackson Heights, Queens. My search, thankfully, ends with Pearl.  My first time here was a few months ago and I made the mistake of telling the waitress to make my meal extra spicy. I erroneously assumed that their dishes were served with very little heat and on the bland side (like most places I have been to in Manhattan). Not here! My meal was super spicy, to the point that I could not fully appreciate the various flavors between the appetizer, entree, Masala tea and naan. The water was fabulous though!  Yesterday I went back for my second time and ordered the same dishes I had during my first visit. Everything was delicious! The meal had a good amount of heat and the flavors were nicely balanced all throughout. The portions are generous and I gladly brought home my leftovers. During my first visit, I drank so much water that I did not pay attention to how much of my meal I did not eat, which was quite a bit.  It is worth noting that for both visits, the service was excellent and the bathroom was clean.  I will be back soon, hopefully this time with friends.
